Upstream sources
----------------

Laterita incorporates and adapts code from two upstream projects:

1. OpenJDK (https://openjdk.org/)
   Licensed under GPLv2 with the Classpath Exception.
   Files derived from OpenJDK retain their original copyright headers
   and license notices. Modifications made for Laterita are likewise
   GPLv2 + Classpath Exception.

2. The Rust Project (https://www.rust-lang.org/)
   Dual-licensed under MIT OR Apache-2.0.
   Files derived from Rust are taken under the MIT option (Apache-2.0
   is not GPLv2-compatible). Original MIT copyright and permission
   notices are preserved verbatim in the affected files.


Rules for adding third-party code
---------------------------------

Any new third-party code added to this repository must be license-
compatible with GPLv2 + Classpath Exception. Acceptable source
licenses include, but are not limited to:

  - GPLv2 (with or without the Classpath Exception)
  - LGPLv2 / LGPLv2.1
  - MIT / X11
  - 2-clause and 3-clause BSD
  - ISC
  - Code dual-licensed "MIT OR Apache-2.0" (taken under the MIT half)

The following are NOT compatible and must not be added:

  - Apache-2.0 only (incompatible with plain GPLv2 due to its patent
    termination clause)
  - GPLv3 / AGPLv3 only (incompatible with GPLv2-only downstream)
  - Any proprietary or source-available-but-not-Free license

Every imported file must retain its original copyright notice and
license header. Record the source URL and commit/version in the commit
message that introduces the file.
